AIRMAIL-Postage-
-Six cents (6c) first ounce and
Six
cents each additional ounce
to any point in the United
States.
AIR EXPRESS-Lowest Air express rates are in effect.
Send for General Air Express tariff, or inquire at any
Varney Air Transport office or any Postal Telegraph
Office.
BAGGAGE 35 pounds free of charge.
Excess baggage
shall be at the rate per pound of ½ of 1% of the pub-
lished air passenger fare.
CHILDREN-Under two years of age when held in arms
carried free.
GROUND TRANSPORTATION-To and from airport
available at all cities, at passengers' expense.
PASSAGE-Cancellation
by
Company-
-Company
re-
serves the right to cancel bookings before passage or
en route at any time such action is deemed advisable or
necessary.
In all events the passengers' sole recourse
shall be the recovery of the unused air fare.
PASSAGE—Cancellation by
Passenger—To secure refund,
ticket must be surrendered at Company office or author-
ized AGENT at least TWO HOURS before scheduled
departure.
REFUNDS-Made at MAIN OFFICE of COMPANY at
El Paso, Texas.
RESERVATIONS—-Reservations
made
only upon pay-
ment of fare.
ROUND TRIPS-Sold at 10% Discount. Return limit 60
days.
STOP OVERS-Allowed for 10 days at any point on the
system.
TIME TABLES-All published schedules show the times
at which planes may be expected to arrive or depart, but
their arrival and departure
guaranteed.
